      "source": "gate:judgment_axis_rollback_sensitive",
      "source_status": "needs_evidence",
      "summary": "Rollback and rollout plan is bounded for immutable npm releases",
      "reason": "Disable the post-merge workflow, revert generated documentation commits, and restore Cloudflare last-known-good. Published npm versions are immutable and are never deleted or overwritten; recovery converges tags only after matching gitHead. Version-unchanged behavior stops after docs deployment, and focused tests cover beta upgrade plus mismatch rejection.",
